<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f107656408489963>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=4606&mid=107656408489963>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=4606&mid=107656408489963>Which Ice Giants drop this</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=4606&mid=107656408489963#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 12th 12:34 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=237139><span id=Scholar>gollumum</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>39 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>After checking this site I went to Everfrost and killed a number of Ice Giants and never got this to drop.&nbsp;&nbsp;After talking to another PC who was camping the &quot;hall&quot; I got the impression that it does not drop off of the IG'S in Everfrost.  He told me that he has killed hundreds of them and had never seen the block of permafrost drop.  I called on a few great guildies to see if they wanted to help me to kill the giants inside Permafrost, they showed up and we headed in to Permafrost and proceeded to kill all the IG'S around Vox's lair.  Within about 20 minutes another PC who happened to be in an alliance guild showed up and joined us, and not much longer I got my block of permafrost from an a Ice Giant.  On the next pull, another block dropped which the new guy took for a fellow guildie.  The time that we spent killing IG's was about 1/2 hour, so I don't believe that this is a rare drop, unless you are killing the IG's in Everfrost =)  Also on another note, there are other IG's in Permafrost who hang out near Vox that don't drop the block such as the Diplomat's and the Priests.  All of these giants seem to have a TON of hp, so beware.  And finally, to sum up this story, I feel one can assume that the Block of Permafrost does NOT drop off of the IG's in Everfrost but instead drops off the ones inside Permafrost.<br><br>P.S. While you're in Permafrost remember to kill some of the Gobby Wizards to get your Heart of Frost which you also need for epic.  <img border=0 src=/shared/smilies/grin.gif><br><br>Well, I hope this helps some of you and saves you some time, so good luck to all of you brave warriors on getting your epic!!</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Gollumum Gnollkiller<br>&lt;Circle of Knowledge&gt;<br>65 Warrior Lanys T'vyl<br><br>Rizzen<br>20 Paladin<br>Butcherblock EQ2<br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=934784" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=934784</a></td></tr>
